import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('year')['net_generation'].sum().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['net_generation'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the trend of net generation over the years?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    grouped_data = data.groupby('source')['net_generation'].sum()
    grouped_data.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    data_pivot = data.pivot(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation')
    
    data_pivot.plot.area(stacked=True)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of net generation by source over the years?")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    data.boxplot(column='net_generation', by='source')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of net generation for each source?")
    plt.suptitle("")
    plt.xlabel("Source")
    plt.ylabel("Net Generation")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
